news.title: Telangana RERA fines Googee Properties for selling plots in unregistered venture
news.para: Telangana RERA has penalized Googee Properties ₹27 lakh for illegally marketing and selling plots in their 'satellite township' without proper registration or approvals. The developer collected advances from buyers under a 'pre-launch offer' for the undeveloped project. RERA has ordered refunds with interest to the complainants and mandated immediate project registration, halting all sales activities until compliance.

news.title: Kerala RERA allows flat-owners to takeover apartments under construction
news.para: K-RERA has made a groundbreaking decision, empowering a flat allottees association to assume control of an unfinished apartment complex in Angamaly. MIR CINTRA's allottees, after the promoter's failure to complete the project despite collecting ₹15.06 crore, can now revive it by pooling funds. This order marks a significant victory for homebuyers in Kerala.

news.title: Yogayatan knocks on NCLT's doors over lenders' decision to allow revised bids for Lavasa
news.para: Yogayatan Group has filed a petition with the NCLT, opposing the lenders' decision to allow revised resolution plans for Lavasa Corp after Yogayatan emerged as the highest bidder. The company fears that Valor Estates' increased bid after the initial offers were opened could compromise the integrity and timeline of the CIRP process.

news.title: Punjab cabinet gives nod to denotify land pooling policy
news.para: The Punjab Cabinet has approved the denotification of the land pooling policy, previously withdrawn due to opposition and court intervention. Amendments to the Punjab Cooperative Societies Act were also approved, removing stamp duty exemptions for certain societies. Additionally, the creation of a 'Panchayat Development Secretary' post and approval for committees overseeing crop procurement and pay commission recommendations were granted.

news.title: China's new home price declines persist but narrow modestly in major cities
news.para: China's new home prices continued their decline in July, dropping 0.3% month-on-month, although the rate of decrease slowed slightly in major cities. Despite various stimulus measures and calls for market stabilization, a sustained recovery remains elusive. Local governments are implementing incentives like relaxed provident fund rules and subsidies to boost homebuying.

news.title: UK's Unite Group to buy Empiric Student Property in $860 million deal
news.para: Unite Group is set to acquire Empiric Student Property for $860.6 million, creating a $14 billion student housing giant in the UK. This deal comes as UK university acceptances reach record highs, driven by increased international student interest due to restrictive visa policies in the U.S. and Australia. The combined portfolio will be worth 10.

news.title: JSW Cement's shares end nearly one per cent lower after muted market debut
news.para: JSW Cement's shares experienced a volatile debut, opening above the IPO price of Rs 147 but ultimately closing with a slight discount on both BSE and NSE. The IPO, which was oversubscribed 7.77 times, aimed to raise funds for a new cement unit in Rajasthan and debt repayment. Market valuation of the company stood at Rs 19,911.94 crore.

news.title: Kalpataru's sales bookings rise 83% to ₹1,249 crore in Q1 FY26
news.para: Kalpataru Ltd witnessed a significant surge in sales bookings, reaching Rs 1,249 crore during the first quarter of this fiscal year, marking an 83% increase driven by higher realization. Despite a decrease in sales volume to 0.56 million sq ft, the average sales realization doubled to Rs 22,476 per sq ft.

news.title: Brigade Enterprises' sales bookings up 3% to ₹1,118 crore in Q1 FY26
news.para: Brigade Enterprises saw a 3% rise in sales bookings, reaching Rs 1,118 crore this fiscal first quarter. Volume decreased, but sales realization per square foot increased. The company's consolidated net profit jumped 79% to Rs 149.88 crore for the quarter ended in June. Total income also increased significantly. Brigade Group, established in 1986, operates across multiple sectors and cities.

news.title: Karnataka: Bill proposing online registration of government-allotted land, mortgages passed
news.para: Karnataka Assembly passed a bill enabling online land registration for government-allotted properties and bank mortgages, using digital signatures to bypass manual processes. Revenue Minister Krishna Byre Gowda highlighted the move aims to curb irregularities and automate loan closure updates.

news.title: Deadline set to clear demolition waste from roads & vacant plots in Gurugram
news.para: ULB Minister Vipul Goel has instructed MCG officials to remove three lakh metric tonnes of C&D waste within a month and resolve the stray cattle problem in 15 days. Rajesh Khullar emphasized keeping Gurgaon clean and directed officials to address garbage and waterlogging issues, while the MCG is working on waste management and sewage solutions.

news.title: Zaheerabad smart city infrastructure works to begin soon
news.para: Zaheerabad Industrial Smart City (ZISC) is poised to begin infrastructure works in the coming months, aiming to attract significant investments and generate numerous jobs. The project, part of the Hyderabad-Nagpur Industrial Corridor, has received necessary approvals and is being developed in phases, with Phase I spanning 3,245 acres.

news.title: Panels set up in April, but survey held up as Haryana yet to define ‘forest’
news.para: Haryana is yet to define 'forest' despite a Supreme Court order. This delay has stalled surveys and mapping of forest areas. Expert committees were formed in April but cannot begin work without the definition. Activists allege the government is deliberately avoiding protecting the Aravalis. The Supreme Court will hear the case on September 9.

news.title: KIADB under fire for move to divert Hebbal transit hub land to private developer
news.para: Karnataka Industrial Area Development Board faces criticism. It transferred land in Hebbal to a private developer. The land was for a Bangalore Metro Rail Corporation Limited project. This decision reduces space for a transport hub. People accuse the government of favoring real estate.

news.title: Developers write to Gujarat government for uniformity in registration fee
news.para: Ahmedabad's redevelopment sector faces hurdles due to inconsistent registration processes. Developers are burdened by varying registration fees, with some offices charging 1% of the agreement value instead of a flat fee. The association urges the government to standardize the process, ensuring clarity on stamp duty and registration fees to facilitate smoother project execution.

news.title: Gurugram: Vacant for 15 years, 1,000 affordable flats to be repaired & allotted
news.para: Gurugram's Sector 47 EWS flats will not be demolished. Haryana Shahari Vikas Pradhikaran will renovate the 1,088 flats. These flats were built in 2010 but never allotted. Advocate Abhay Jain filed a complaint. The Prime Minister's Office intervened. Renovation work is sanctioned with Rs 8 crore. Allotment will happen after the renovation. The original plan was to auction the land.

news.title: DDA to launch premium housing scheme by August-end
news.para: The Delhi Development Authority is set to launch its Premium Housing Scheme 2025 by the end of August, featuring around 250 flats and parking spaces across various Delhi localities through e-auctioning. This scheme includes HIG, MIG, and LIG flats with prices varying accordingly.

news.title: Vadodara: 19th century Indumati Palace to be flanked by upscale apartments
news.para: The 145-year-old Indumati Palace in Vadodara, owned by Pratapsinhrao Gaekwad, is set to be developed into a residential and commercial complex. Six 12-storey buildings will be constructed around the palace, which will be restored and converted into a clubhouse for residents.
